article.headline: Purdue 78, Coppin St. 57
article.story: WEST LAFAYETTE, Ind. -- Robbie Hummel scored 17 of his 24 points in the second half and Purdue defeated Coppin State 78-57 on Saturday. Hummel added eight rebounds for the Boilermakers (6-1), who won their 21st straight home game. Ryne Smith added 14 points, Terone Johnson 11 and Anthony Johnson 10. Lewis Jackson had 10 assists. Purdue racked up a 32-8 advantage in bench points. Tony Gallo led Coppin State (1-4) with 17 points and eight assists. Akeem Ellis scored 12 points. Coppin State trimmed a 15-point first-half deficit to 48-43 with 14:08 remaining, but the Boilermakers turned to Hummel, who scored eight in a row -- including a pair of 3-pointers -- and Purdue eventually opened a 61-46 lead with 9:13 to play. Coppin State got no closer than 13 thereafter as Purdue finished the game with a 25-11 run.
